storyInfo: Times change, and so do the people we used to know. That's how an average seafood hawker became a 'key man.' He knows in his heart what he lost on his way here and what he must protect on the road ahead.

attributes.content: Lou sai, all our sashimi comes freshly sliced. You don't get fresher fins than that. All our finballs are hand-kneaded, too. You don't get chewier balls than that. Line up in the back there.
attributes.name: Jaye
Jaye
attributes.content: Lou...

attributes.name: Jaye
attributes.content: Waai Fu?
I'm delivering something for Uncle Lee. Just passing by.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: You've had your stall here the last couple days? No wonder I haven't seen you.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Th-The docks get lots of traffic. Finballs sell like hotcakes here.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The only ones around at this hour are workers on their way home. You sure you can move more finballs here than the tourist spots?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Never mind. You're about to close up, right? Let's head back together. I'll wait for you.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Uh... I'm okay...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Huh? What's wrong?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: N-Nothing. Well... Waai Fu, I... I've got something for you.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I, well, it's a graduation present...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: A graduation present? Now?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Stop by my place when you have time. There's a spare key under the doormat.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: There's a big box in the bedroom. It's all in there, along with a couple things I wanted to tell you...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I've had it prepared for a while, but after you graduated, you went to Shangshu and Yumen. I haven't had a lot of chances to give them to you, since you were hardly ever in Lungmen.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Don't forget to stop by.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I should probably say thank you... but this is really weird. Who makes a girl fetch her own present?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Yeah, well... Say, isn't it your birthday on Saturday? Let me take you to the movies, and I'll bring the graduation present along with the one for your birthday.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You go home and get some rest now. I'll meet you at the mall tomorrow morning.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Ahem, lou sai.
You selling your finballs or not?
Oh, deoi m zyu.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: An order of finballs, double spice, yeah? Coming right up.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Sure.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Your finballs.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: That's the friend you said knows her kung fu, right? Surname Waai?
Yeah.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: And she just graduated?
Yeah.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I'm thinking I could let her join the gang. A talented girl with solid moves. You don't get help like that easy.
Don't be stupid, Ah Wei.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I don't want her getting mixed up in this.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Alright... You're still worried.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: You don't trust me, huh? I told you already. We've got everyone here from the highest echelon to the bottom rung in our pockets. As long as these goods make it through the docks safe tonight, they'll disappear into the slums tomorrow morning. Nothing will happen.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Say you toss some limestone into the river ahead of us. When it's all dark out, who'll notice the bubbles on the surface?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I'm just a little nervous.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Yeah, I get it. It's your first time. You'll get used to it.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I told you. There is no next time.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Fine, fine. How's prep work going for your first and last time, then?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: The driver, inspector, and court clerk are all old friends, and I've already talked to them.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Tonight, all the cargo ships entering port will, coincidentally, have to go through a monthly inventory check and sorting, and because of the huge amount of cargo, from 10:00 to 10:30, the port will temporarily halt inspections of incoming cargo ships.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Have your ship come in at 10:15. You have fifteen minutes to unload your goods.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Have those ships greet us.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: You don't trust me?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: This has nothing to do with that, Jaye. Show me.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: How do you want them do it?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Have the ship furthest to the left in the docks blink twice.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Uncle Fung, turn the searchlight on and off twice.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Let me hear the rightmost ship's whistle. Let's see if it's loud enough.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Big Cheung, blow the whistle twice for me, please.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: And have the ship in the middle head out for a quick spin?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Siu Kai, sorry. Help me out here.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I heard you guys... Heading out this late at night... You know that favor I owe you? We'll call it even with this.
Jaye, you may just be a seafood hawker, but you're the most reliable, promising seafood hawker in all of Lungmen!
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Remember what I told you when we were kids? When the two of us work together, anything's possible.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Even a simple drink has uses beyond imagination.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: They're all good guys. They have no idea what they're getting mixed up in.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I mean, remember what the adults in the neighborhood used to say when we were kids? 'There's no good or bad. There's only relationship.' Lungmen is a place where we talk relationship.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: That's a whole 'nother thing.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Anyway, I made the right call coming to you.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Twenty days earlier...
Phew—
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Lou sai, can I trade this for an order of finballs?
Sorry, I'm closed for the day—
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The man sets an empty can down on the cutting board in front of Jaye.
The entire bottom side of the can is cut off, and the can is cut twice along an axis and bent outward into a curve, revealing its dark, silver interior.
It looks like a crude flower or something.
Ah Wei?!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Hey, Jaye. Been a while.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: It really is you! When did you get back? How did you find me? It's been at least a decade since the last time we saw each other, right? Where did you go after you left Lungmen?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I came looking for you right after I made my way back here. As for how I found you...
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Don't forget you took on two whole gangs all by yourself. Everybody in Lungmen knows you. They call you 'stone-faced finball bossman,' 'ice-cold Jaye,' and stuff.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: That was just an accident... Stop making fun of me.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The man picks up the carved can, on which the light of the street is faintly reflected.
I didn't think you'd still remember.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Of course I do.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: When we were in third grade, you brought a bunch of empty cans home with you, and your mom scolded you for bringing back trash. But then you used them to make little trinkets like this, fixed the antenna, and got the broken TV working again.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Metal strengthens signals, and I was just tinkering.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Ever since, you scoured the alleyways and collected empty cans. One day, you would make an incense holder. The next day, a communications terminal. You saved your family lots of money.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I even took you in as my goon. You followed me everywhere.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Yeah, our houses were right next to each other. The neighbors liked to compare us, but they always complimented you, said you'd do great things when you grew up. I was jealous.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Not like me... I'm not nearly as bright, so all I could do was learn how to make finballs from Uncle Tung.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: So, are you just visiting, or are you staying for good this time?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Nah, I'm staying.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Great! I've been helping clean your place. It's in pretty good shape. Just move some furniture, toiletries, and stuff in and you can start...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Yeah, Jaye, I need your help.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Huh?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I brought a shipment of goods back to Lungmen to sell.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Nice! So you're in business now. Lungmen's pretty strict with inspections, but I can help you run them by the L.G.D.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: My goods aren't on the L.G.D.'s list of approved imports and exports.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Y-You're smuggling?!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Weapons? Originium products? Illegal drugs? What's with the hands. Is that some kind of signal? I-I don't know what you're getting at.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Nobody knows about this. We've been planning it for a while. It's all under wraps, I guarantee.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Besides, the risk and return are proportional. Jaye, I know you know the guys at the docks.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I've been away from Lungmen for over a decade. I don't know the place anymore. I need money, and I need to do this deal to get back on my feet. You're the only one who can help.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: No, I'm not doing it. You shouldn't, either.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Oh yeah. Why did you come around in the end again?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: It's ten after ten... The ship is about to come in.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Where are the guys picking up the merch? Have them stand by at the port. We've only got fifteen minutes.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Don't worry. Just a little longer.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Officer Hoshiguma, it's almost time. Why is it still quiet?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Maybe we got a bad tip?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Relax. We can trust this informant.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Hallucinatory drugs made from purified Originium... No one in the Lungmen black markets would dare deal in something like this. Why is someone smuggling something this hot all of a sudden?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: The Rat King hasn't been taking his usual walks, has he?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: I heard he was hurt bad on his trip to Yumen. Do you mean...?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Lin Yühsia isn't going to Victoria anymore. But I doubt her plan to become the 'Lin the Violet' is gonna go all that smooth.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Looks like there are some fussy folks who want to find out for the old man whether his daughter is worthy of his chair.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: The gangs in the slums, big and small, have been making lots of noise, and the L.G.D. has been busy with all that.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: But I guess these folks have forgotten the L.G.D.'s hard stance against contraband.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: 10:16. Fourteen minutes left.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The ship's docked. On the double, everyone. Watch your surroundings, and keep two men on watch.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I didn't expect you to have so many guys on this job.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Why not? This is a huge deal. Lots of hands want a slice of the pie.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Jaye, you look nervous.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: You keep watch here. I'll go check things out.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Alright.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: *sigh*... Ah Wei, the ship's that way. Why are you heading for the exit?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Officer Hoshiguma, should we move in?
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Hold on. These are no normal gangsters. They're on high alert. Wait until they fall into our trap. We'll catch both the men and the goods together.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: We're not letting any of these drugs into Lungmen. And we're not letting a single perp escape.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Understood.
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Remember to keep the informant safe.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Officer! Looks like the boss is trying to run!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Not a chance!
attributes.name: L.G.D. Officer

attributes.content: Wait! He's definitely just testing...
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Ah Wei! Don't run! You can't!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: All units, move in!
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Jaye keeps running.
He most likely bumped into a few passersby, and he definitely knocked over the fruit stand on the street corner. He keeps muttering, 'deoi m zyu,' but he doesn't stop.
His friend is right ahead. His friend is still running.

He has no time to even think about which streets he has been running through. He notices nothing except how there are less and less people, the roads are getting narrower, and his surroundings are getting quieter. So quiet, he can hear nothing but his and his friend's panting.
The oxygen deprivation is causing him to hallucinate.
Jaye starts to think he is running down that alley he used to run down as a kid—
He is following his 'Soda Can Magician' friend, through the shades of the banyan trees and out the slums, as they both planned to go together, towards a brighter future.
S-Stop running. My lungs are about to blow.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: There's nowhere to go up ahead... It's a dead end.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Ah Wei.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You sold me out.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I got a good thing going on, and you're the first one I went to with it.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I know you're a coward for how mean you look. You're a good guy, and all you wanna do is sell fins and finballs. I get that. You turning down the offer? I was fine with that. That's no skin off my back.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I did have my suspicions when you came back to me a week later and said you were in. But you're Jaye. I knew Jaye would follow me, just like he used to when we were kids.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: We never kept anything from each other. You even taught me the knife skills you learned from Uncle Tung. I never lied to you, and you never lied to me.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: But this time, you were lying to me right from the start.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Ah Wei, l-listen...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Who are you snitching for? Another gang? The L.G.D.?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Two weeks ago...
How's business been?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Officer Hoshiguma?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Do you need something from me?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Well, I'm sure you wouldn't believe me if I told you I was just passing by and decided to get a couple of orders of finballs for my lads back at the station.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: That would've been nice, wouldn't it?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I thought I'd stop by to give you a heads up. The Char Sius and Lou Seois' bosses are about to be released.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: They're scum, but they're still gangsters. You threw a wrench in their plans, and they lost face among the Lungmen triads, thanks to you. They just might make trouble for you.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Oh—
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: No need to be scared. The L.G.D. can offer you protection, if you want.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Yeah, thanks, Officer. Here's an order of finballs. It's on me. Have a nice day.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I'm not done yet. Are you merchants always so afraid to deal with the L.G.D.?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Heh.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I want to ask you about something.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Have you been to the ports lately?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: I went just this morning to settle my bill for the month.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Have you seen anyone or anything suspicious?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Suspicious, huh...?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Anyone who's been asking about the ships, policies on the flow of goods, inspection procedures, that sort of thing.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Officer, is something going on? That port is the biggest seafood market in Lungmen. If something happens and the stalls at the market get shut down, everyone's gonna be out of a job...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Relax. I'm just hypothesizing here.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: According to our sources, someone is about to smuggle a shipment of illegal drugs into the slums.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: The L.G.D. caught wind of it a little too late, and the shipment might already have made it into Lungmen. We're investigating all logistics channels right now... The gateway, city beltway, the port.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: (And he said it's all under wraps...)
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: What?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Oh, nothing.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Anyway, you know the port better than I do, so I want you to pay attention to the people there and see if there's any movement. If you notice anything, give me a call.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Yeah, I will.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: This's pretty serious, right, Officer?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: What do you mean?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Is this smuggling case serious?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The detectives have this shipment listed as highly dangerous illegal contraband. It's on a whole other level from the Originium Devices that the Char Sius removed from those weapons to sell.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: If you find anything... you have my number.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Well, off I go then. Thanks for the finballs.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Hold on, Officer Hoshiguma.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: So you snitched on me to the L.G.D. and started spying for them?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I did it because...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: It's all gone. I put a whole decade of savings into this deal! And now it's all gone!
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Well, I guess it's for the best.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Who ever said Jaye's a coward, a small man, an ordinary guy? You're way more of a badass than the undercover cops in the triad shows. They're all acting, but you're the real deal, as brave as it gets.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Calm down. Hear me out.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I don't want to hear another word from you. Later. We'll pretend I never came back.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Ah Wei, I can't let you go just like that.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: What more do you want? The successful sting's not good enough for you? You want to take the perp in yourself, too?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: What, are they going to name you citizen of the month?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Go look over there.
attributes.name: Distant Voice

attributes.content: Search through every one of these alleyways. Don't let anyone get away.
attributes.name: Distant Voice

attributes.content: Jaye, move.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Your plan's a bust. Your buyers won't let you off easy. You're in with some merciless guys.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: That's why I'm leaving Lungmen right now.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I'm not letting you go.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Hmph... Don't say I didn't warn—Hm?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: I swiped your weapon back at the port.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You remember how we never held any grudges against each other for more than a day? Every time we had a difference of opinion, we worked through it the same way.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Like this!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Jaye punches his friend square in the face.
So anyone involved in this smuggling operation will get a much harsher sentence than the Char Sius and the Lou Seois?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: That's right.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Like... how harsh are we talking?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: All the guys wanted to do last time was sell crude, shoddy Originium products. Besides, you busted them halfway through, and they also owned up to the whole thing with a pretty good attitude throughout, so they got light sentences.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: That said, the bosses still got two years in the can.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: But if our intel's correct, they're smuggling some powerful hallucinogens. On paper, they're just very hard to get 'painkillers' and 'sedatives' that work fast.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: But, of course, they don't come with any instructions, and they don't tell the users about any potential side effects—that the trace amounts of purified Originium can accelerate the deterioration of Oripathy.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Th-That's dirty money.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: It's gonna make the patients severely dependent.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: The Lungmenites tormented by sickness will have both their last pennies and last breaths of life sucked dry. They'll bring a herd infection that's even more uncontrollable.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: That's why the L.G.D. has always enforced hard on this kind of contraband, and even the triads rarely deal in this stuff.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: The mastermind will have to spend the rest of his life behind bars.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: That's a serious crime...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Then what if it's only attempted? Would that make any difference? What if they turn themselves in? Does that make the sentence any lighter?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Where did you learn all that...?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: T-Tell me, Officer.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: If it hasn't caused any severe, irreparable harm yet, then there's still room to turn things around.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: But even if they manage to escape, if they have a criminal record, they'll never be allowed to in Lungmen again.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Can't come back to Lungmen, huh?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Alright, Jaye, I've answered all your questions.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Now it's your turn to tell me what you know.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Officer Hoshiguma, I want you to help a friend of mine.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You don't have to help me, but you didn't have to backstab me like that!
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Ah Wei, I am helping you!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: A series of muffled, rhythmic sounds can be heard. Deep in the back alley, the two men exchange blows.
Like some kind of silly, turn-based game.
You used to make antennas, incense holders, and comms terminals out of soda cans.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You were the 'Soda Can Magician,' you were my hero, you were so smart. Just an amazing guy.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You should never have gone down this path!
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Do you know why I had to leave Lungmen all those years ago? You probably heard that my family ran into some kind of trouble, but you have no idea what exactly happened, right?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: It was a stupid gang fight. Two sides had a turf war and got into it, and the bosses had to send in guys to clean things up.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: My parents just happened to pass by. We had nothing to do with the triads. Why would we?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Do you know who was in charge of the cleanup? Why do you think I left Lungmen without so much as coming to say good bye?
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: ...Uncle Tung.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: 'Soda Can Magician?' Magician my ass!
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: In Lungmen, soda cans get kicked around and dumped in trash cans.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: But I don't blame you. You're Jaye. This has nothing to do with you. It doesn't even have anything to do with Uncle Tung. Because this is Lungmen. 'There's no good or bad. All that matters is survival.'
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: You know, even if you didn't join me on this gig, once I had the money, I was going to help you franchise your finball stall.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: We were going to take those finballs all over the country. Shangshu, Jiangqi, Yumen. Even beyond Yan.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Jaye takes a few punches and slowly backs up against the wall. He steps on something, slips, and falls to the ground.
I don't need that.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Living on dirty money... I can't have that on my conscience.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Ah Wei, you know that people could die because of those drugs you were smuggling, right?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I don't know what you've been through over the last ten years. I'm sure you've done all sorts of things to survive. Everybody's got a different way to get by, right?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You don't have to have lots of money. You don't have to be in a position of power.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Has Lungmen really changed? The slums, the port, the park, the seafood market... There are so many folks here, trying their hardest, living life without hurting anybody.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You're such an amazing guy. What's stopping you from doing that?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I can help you.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: I'm tired. I-I've got nothing left to say.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Jaye lies down on the ground. A stream of blood gushes out of his forehead and wells up in the corner of his eye.
He shuts his eye hard to keep the blood from flowing into his eye. He has always looked like a pretty mean guy, and with how his face is bloodied, he now looks all the more ferocious.
*sigh*—
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Goodbye.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: The man isn't able to step away. He looks down to find his brother, his eye barely open, clinging to his leg.
Just like when they were both kids, he is a quiet guy, but he is as stubborn as one can be.
Jaye, let go. I really don't want to hurt you.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: Jaye does not answer, nor does he let go.
The man grits his teeth, leans down, and pulls the scaling knife out of Jaye's pocket.
This is your fault.
attributes.name: Ah Wei

attributes.content: All of a sudden, the man finds that he has come face-to-face with Jaye, both of them on the muddy ground. Yet he feels not the slightest bit of cold, perhaps because of the numbness from the intense impact.
The very moment before his consciousness drifts away, he faintly spots a terribly dented soda can. Perhaps that was the thing that crashed into his head mere seconds ago.
Phew—
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Made it just in time.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: That's about the size of it.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: All the merchandise have been recovered. The overseas smugglers and the local recipients have all been taken in by the L.G.D.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Thanks, Madame Oni.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: How are things on your end?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: We may have put a stop to the problem upstream, but those downstream aren't blameless. I put together a list of the ones in the slums waiting to distribute. And I paid each of them a visit before I came here.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: I won't trouble the L.G.D. with our housework.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: Should've expected no less from the 'Lin the Violet,' huh?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: It's nothing. My dad's still resting up after his injuries, and I don't want him to get out of bed.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: Right, he wanted to ask. How was Jaye on this sting?
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: He was hurt, but it was nothing serious.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Without him, we wouldn't have been able to wrap up this operation at the port or round them up so easily.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: If even an ounce of this shipment had made it into Lungmen, things would've got much trickier.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Right.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: Even outside the slums, there are plenty of gangs who would be willing to deal in hallucinatory drugs of this level. Taking care of it all right up front is the safest approach, of course.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: But Jaye's just a normal guy, and given Uncle Tung's age, Dad doesn't want him to...
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: I get it. The situation's unique... but rest assured the L.G.D. will protect its informants.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: And how is Mr. Lin's prognosis?
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Fair. He still wants to sneak outside to play weiqi with his old friends.
attributes.name: Lin Yühsia

attributes.content: Hah.
attributes.name: Hoshiguma

attributes.content: Oh, you're finally awake.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Oww... that's a sharp pain.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Of course it hurts when you do that to your face.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Don't move. I'm putting on some ointment.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: How's Ah Wei?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: The L.G.D. guys took him away.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Speaking of which, Officer Hoshiguma wants you to head to the station for a written statement after you rest up.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: ...Alright.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: So, why were you playing hero behind my back again?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: You went undercover, and on a case where the smugglers are all actual bad guys, not like those Char Siu thugs last time! One of the L.G.D. guys got hurt while they were taking the smugglers in.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Why didn't you ask for my help? You almost lost your life back there, you know?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: I know.
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: (That's why I didn't want to drag you into this...)
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: What are you mumbling about?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Nothing... Say, I thought you were running errands for Mr. Lee? What are you doing back here?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: You were talking funny. I knew something was up.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: And I haven't even asked you yet. You said you had a graduation present for me, and you wrote something down... What is it supposed to mean?
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: Well, I did actually get you a graduation present...
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: How was that talking funny...?
attributes.name: Jaye

attributes.content: Not the graduation present. My birthday.
attributes.name: Waai Fu

attributes.content: It's Sunday, not Saturday. How'd you get that wrong?
attributes.name: Waai Fu
